                "display_name": "salbeira",
                "accept_rate": 45
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1351004814,
            "creation_date": 1351004814,
            "body": "<p>If the user enters a wrong value your method would loop endlessly. If the method does not wait for the JOptionPane to close you will be confronted with an immesurable amount of dialog-popups.<\/p>\n\n<p>You should let the method return a boolean value in any case and change some kind of \"state\", another boolean or some other kind of state-variable, in your programm if it succeeds.<\/p>\n\n<p>If it doesn't you can let your state \"loop\" back to the point where the user has to enter a number and then let him restart the validation process, but in my opinion you should not restart the validation process on it's own when it fails.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 13033536,
            "question_id": 13033178
        }
